HEADWORD: Hygroplasm
<hw>Hy"gro*plasm</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Gr. <?/ wet +
<?/ form, mold.]</ety> <fld>(Biol.)</fld> <def>The fluid portion of the
cell protoplasm, in opposition to <xex>stereoplasm</xex>, the solid or
insoluble portion. The latter is supposed to be partly nutritive and
partly composed of idioplasm.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

